==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[slita]], Old Saxon ''slītan'' (Dutch [[slijten]]), Old High German [[slizan]] (German [[schleißen]]), Old Norse [[slíta]] (Swedish [[slita]]).

